Awesome meal and even Better service!   Thank you for being one of the Best Restaurants in DC!!!
Tried the philly cheesesteak and the tenders. Both were good. Decent size portion. I'll probably return
Nice place. Decent food.
(Translated by Google) Very quaint, friendly staff and tasty food  (Original) Muy pintoresco, personal amable y comida sabrosa
Great pub. Friendly atmosphere.  Good happy hour menu and prices. Near Cannon House Office Building or Capitol South metro stop.
Affordable and diverse menu. Great drinks and comfort food.
The beer was good, service was good.. but there are plenty of pubs with much better food in DC.
Great food and atmosphere but horrible service - if your at a high top order from the bar
First time here, had a guacamole bacon cheeseburger & fries. Good, but the medium rare I ordered arrived as just a shade under well done. We'll see how they do next time.
Delicious food and great service. Can't go wrong with tots and juicy chicken tenders. Great selection of draft beers!
Food is quick and decent, good beer selection.

Not as nice as I thought it would be. The food and service were fine but did not stand out. The bar area appeared nice and attracted a loud Saturday afternoon crowd. Bullfeathers was good but I wouldn't go out of my way to visit again.
Saturday December 7, 2019 walked in at 6:00pm and was sent out by the bar tender on the phone saying she was closed..website says they close at 8:00.
Super fun DC bar. Super cute gals there too. #foxden
Not friendy management
Unique urban atmosphere. For someone who spends most of their time in rural America, this place is not all big city. Enjoyed the food and neighborhood.

The food was good!! The service needed work. I had to get up and get the check myself and take it to another waitress to check out. And the waiter forgot a few things like refills and orders, but had time to stand around and talk to coworkers lol
Food was good. Crabcakes and salmon esp. Fish and chips fair at best. Drink service was slow.
Service is great just sat at the bar and literally there was over 20 fruit flies hovering over me.  15 on the ceiling.  Just gross and it smelled nasty inside.  Please find a way to clean up a bit.
Wait staff is awesome..very pleasant made my visit enjoyable
Go for the tots or the housemade chips. Burgers are great and drinks are well crafted. Bartender Adam was great... I think I'm going to become a regular here!!

The food was good. Not incredible, but good. The service was terrible. We felt like we practically didn’t exist. It took them 10 minutes to even acknowledge we were there, and another 20 before we even saw our waitress again. She never refilled our water, didn’t introduce herself, barely spoke to us, and we only saw her 3 times total in the hour we were there. Would not return and would not recommend. Way too expensive for the poor service we got.
Try a milk shake while you're there.
Nice lunch and beer

This is a great pub for Hill staffers but not so much for Hill visitors, unless the House is out of session. Usually a nice place to stop by after work for a pint and a quick bite, but unless you're lucky or going solo, don't anticipate finding a spot at the bar during session weeks. The food is great, good selection of draft beers, and a nice dark atmosphere that can get fairly loud during busy times. Recommend: Teddy's Tots (best tater tots in DC and a not-so-secret Hill secret) and a Shiner Bock.
Sweet little place to eat. Burger was good. Pizza was really good.
Convienant to stop ...
Good food, but service is always so slow.  Dont go there on your lunch break if you only get an hour.  Better for after work happy hour when theres no time constraints.
DC favorite for workers on the Hill!
Great service, great drinks!
Always a must in DC
The crab cakes were delicious, and the apple cobbler was to die for!!! Great service, too.
Absolutely delicious! The burgers and shakes were awesome.

We visited just before happy hour on a Thursday -- grabbed a few drinks and had a tasty Bacon Jam burger of the week -- amazing! We could see Bullfeathers is a huge hit with the after work crowd: bustling and noisy bar area with plenty of suits blowing off steam at the end of the day. Despite the crowd of regulars, it's still pretty welcoming for visitors with a quiet side area walled off from the bar. Good service and tasty food. Pretty cheap cocktails for DC, too.
Always enjoy Bullfeathers! They tapped several kegs which are happy hour specials but still made is right. Plan to return soon.
The food is delicious.  Can get very busy.
Enjoyed an afternoon lunch with co-workers. The tater tot appetizer was yum! Also got to enjoy the Cajun pasta. Close to house office buildings.
Friendly atmosphere, food was great

Nice close to the capital where you can see all the government works come out and have a few few drink after a long day in the office good beer and noise level in the dinning room just right I had the beet hummus, and the Cuban sandwich good my husband had the Teddy fried chicken dinner it was ok.
Bull feathers was a great place to eat and good choices of food

I really only come here if there is a happy hour or a gathering after work. It is sufficiently ordinary. None of the drinks are going to change your life and the food probably won't either but it's a good spot to mingle with Hill staffers if you're on the House side. I will say it can be crazy busy here most nights after work so keep that in mind if you're looking for fast or efficient service. I don't think I'd call it my favorite happy hour spot around here but it's always a good standby.
Good food, usually.   Bad service, usually.
Slow slow slow service. No one cared that you were there. Thirty minutes on a slow night to get a drink and still didn't take our dinner order so we all left.
Great place for a reception after visiting your Congressional Delegation.
Great service. Good food, just dont mind people sitting on you back litteraly.(no fault of resteraunt just rude person)
Decent food with deplorable service.
Great food and atmosphere
Not impressed pricey and Not a good selection of buffalo wings only spicy hot wings,Tater tots were good
Amazing burgers!
Classic Capitol hill bar
Great place to rest in between rounds of hustling the Hill.
Good food in good service
Not many vegan or gluten free options for my friend.
Burger was fine, the Cuban was luke warm and could use more sauce, and the homemade chips were cold.
Great place to grab a drink while waiting for friends coming in at Capitol South.
Dining outside was wonderful. SERVICE WAS EXCELLENT. BURGERS AND CHICKEN WERE COOKED TO ORDER. BEER IS BEER!

(Translated by Google) Very comfortable to take a break at the foot of the Capitol Hills. Especially the possibility to sit outside is remarkable.  (Original) Sehr gemütlich zum Pause machen am Fuß des Capitol-Hills. Besonders die Möglichkeit draußen zu sitzen ist bemerkenswert.

(Translated by Google) Great. Cozy place, attentive service, great for a happy hour that counts on special prices of drinks for this time  (Original) Excelente. Lugar aconchegante, atendimento atencioso, otimo para um happy hour que conta com preços especiais de bebidas para este horário
Great location. Decent atmosphere.

Great food & service. Was in DC for a couple of days and stopped here after a day of strolling through the National Mall. Every thing was good. The younger ones had pizza and the mini burgers with fries. Wife had Cajun pasta and I had a Cuban sandwich.  Each of sharing a bit with each other.  As I said, it was all good.  Cost a bit, but seems every where in the DC area close to downtown does cost a bit.

Very nice restaurant. I ordered french onion soup and a crab cake. They were both very good. The waiter was very attentive. Made sure we had everything we needed. Decent prices for lunch. Not overly expensive.
Great Fried Chicken
A tweak pricey, but good is great - fries are fabulous - and the place is pleasantly funky. Always a good time and meal.
Perfect place for a delicious lunch!! French Onion soup was delish!!
Large selection of beer on tap served cold and with a smile.
Shakes are amazing!
Poor service.

Not a bad place for lunch. Service is fast, decent menu selection. I miss the old decor as it reminded me of the old DC bar scene, but otherwise not a bad place for a quick lunch bite in the Capitol Hill area.
Overall great place to see people on the Hill get drunk. You'll find Trumpsters here as well. It can get a bit pretentious but you won't be out of place coming here in your work clothes.
Food was good and the drinks on point
sliders were very good.
Very yummy food.
One of the closest bars to the SCOTUS. So when a ruling goes for or against your wishes, celebrate or drown your sorrows.
Hot spot for the scene to be seen. Andy the bartender is awesome. Food service at tables is slow.
Great soup!!
Great food fast.
Food was not that good service was so bad and long
Pretty great food and good atmosphere
Tasty cobb.

Didn't dine in, just carry out. Ordered some wings. I also ordered a side of fries but I don't think that came across to the person who took my order. Thankfully I wasn't charged for it because I didn't received any.  The wings were alright. I'd probably wouldn't buy the 10 wings again because of the price. But the people were nice inside and it was a great atmosphere for the time I was there.  They also need to fix the front door. Unless it's supposed to slam heavy every time the door closes. Most annoying part of the trip.
Good food and service.   Drinks tasted weak (lack of alcohol)
Exceptionally good food!
We had a private party for 40 and Bullfeathers pulled it off perfectly. Great simple well executed food.  Everyone had a blast. We will be back!!!
mediocre food, bad service.  wouldbt be in business if not for the location
Great food and service
Excellent food and clean establishment. The staff is so friendly and nice
Close to the capitol building with a good drink and food selection, but doesn't have a great happy hour deal.

Went with a large group that had reservations. Got half the orders wrong and then were so slow serving... that the kids only got 10 mins to eat before we had to leave. What was served was good tasting though.
Good drinks

Totally loved the food and service in this place.  Food was typical bar food.  They have a full bar with lots of great beers.  The bartender took great care of us.  Great service and pointed us in the right direction for quality microbrews.  Next we are in DC we'll be back.
This is one of the best bars in DC for drinks and atmosphere and service I’m from Alabama and felt like I was at home Thanks to all the staff this place rocks
Great food. Quick service..
We visited on a slow night after just getting in town and it was pouring. Service was friendly and the food was good. Americana style as others have stated.
Good spot for a nice lunch when down in capitol hill, but off the main areas.
It remains as one of the "go to" places when visiting DC.

The food was juicy and flavorful. Although the wait is somewhat long, it is not as long as fast food restaurants and regular restaurants half it's talent!!!! I recommend this place to anyone wanting a yummy filling meal!
Great service,I order salmon but it's contain some polythin but they replaced immdiatly Food was delicious very busy place
Great food, BBQ salmon was great. Brownie Sundae was a great finish. Will be back the next time in town.

Classic Hill bar and restaurant. The food is typical bar food and the bar is really long. It's a fine place to stop if you're looking for very basic Americana food. It's more of a go with a crowd for drinks type of place and when you get hungry get some apps.  Always feel free to reach out to me on Twitter @joerazz

I went alone after having a scary day. My waiter was kind, helpful, and understanding. I informed him that I had been assaulted on the mall and wasn't sure what metro mine to take or when, but that I wanted to be back at my hotel before dark due to being so shaken up. He showed me the lines, told me which to take and when, and told me that he was sorry that such a thing happened. He helped my visit be a tad better with the circumstances.  The food was delicious and to my expectations. You should really try it out.
Great food and great service
Bullfeathers is a D.C. institution. It's worth a visit for who you might see more than what you can eat. But, the chicken sandwich is good.

The food was OK. The salmon casear salad's dressing tasted like mayonnaise. Not a big deal, but I was a little disappointed. Other items I've gotten previously have been good. Service is fast and friendly.
Good food and drinks.  Always a good time there
Food is decent. Service could use improvement. Waitstaff was unpleasant. Restaurant is kind of dirty.
Pretty good at the lunch rush. Plenty of options and decent service.
Great place
Good place for a reception or fundraiser!

This is a busy place with a nice selection of beverages and food. I had a salad here which was very tasty. The bad points are the fact that the outdoor seats are a bit uncomfy to sit in (there are no pillows on the metal chairs) and the restrooms are not clean.
Decent beer selection.  Decent food
Perfect place for cocktails or beers. The food is on point even if the menu is a little pricey. The bartenders and servers were phenomenal and very friendly.

Bullfeathers is a typical congressional staffers after work hangout, just down 1st street from the House office buildings. The food is American. The drinks are honest. The prices are reasonable. The service is reasonable. What else do you need to know? I have been coming here for years.

Good service but not super quick if you're in a hurry. Plan on spending about an hour there on the short side. Fish and Chips was good but not the best I have had. The Burger and club sandwich at my table looked tasty.
Food is pretty good. This is your average American Food pub. People like to hang outside the door and smoke. I gave it 3 stars instead of 4 for this reason.
Decent food.
Best in town
Great place
Great food. Great pub
Convenient to Capital.
Way too many neckties, food an service solid.
Great service.  Good food.  Fun atmosphere
Extremely slow service with mediocre food and high prices.
Pretty good food. We went during a busy lunch hour and they sat us within 15 minutes.
Food was good, but took 40 minutes after ordering. The service was poor. Drink refills were not offered, and we had to go ask for silverware after our food came.
Pretty good. Menu seemed surprisingly limited, but food was fine. Good service, fries were hot on arrival (important).
Great location.  Average service.
GREAT food and services
Good pizza and drinks and happy hour
Great food, quick service. Never disappointed.
Sriracha wings were blah and cold when I received them and over cooked
It's the perfect place to kick back with friends after a long day on the Hill.
Great food and service for family or to dine alone
Good food, good service
Very historical restaurant great food great service if you're in the area stop by
Excellent food and service by far. The meal was some what pricey but the quality was excellent.
Ok American fare. Decent little pub
Great food and service
Great Food! And Adam was the most awesome waiter imaginable! Pay him visit!
Good food but absolutely huge burgers! I love a good sloppy burger, but these quickly become a pile of stuff on the plate. Still delicious but get ready

Awesome food and such great service the chef there is amazing he personally goes around to each table and makes sure that the food and everything coming out of his kitchen is top notch, you simply dont find many people who take so much pride in their work and just overall service to people.
Cool low key. Old school vibe.
Great Happy Hour specials and good beer selection

Food was sub part at best. Server was disinterested in his job. Place was mostly empty but we still had to ask for water multiple times to get water for everyone in the party of 4. And hey it boasts itself as the spot where lobbiests go and what not... I guess they want to hang out with their own kind and by that I mean we were all bitten by mosquitoes while indoors. So if you want meh food, bad service and want to deal with blood suckers, this is your spot.
Awesome food & service
Great place and good food if you have to spend time near the Capitol.
Food was outstanding but "policy" won't allow for separate checks.
Very good America style food, geeat service.  Always busy, make reservations
Fun little restaurant nestled in the residential area of DC.
Great relaxing place.
This place is great to relax and enjoy your day! Thank you and God bless!
Great food in a classic, historic dc bar setting.  Can be crowded and loud during happy hour or around dinner time, but the food is very good.
Good food, good service, good menu, solid place to eat
Ruben was good. At $13 for lunch, a tad pricey,  but I would get again.
Where whiney GOPers go to whine.
My cheeseburger was great!
Great Food!
fast service for small groups

A great little pub with a menu far beyond pub food. They don't skimp on portions but they don't overdo it either. Delicious food and a decent variety of beers on tap. Casual atmosphere and friendly staff. Just a stone's throw from congressional offices and tourist stops located on a picturesque street.
Great location, good food. Love the outdoor seating.
Hill bar. It's big but bartenders are slow. Good beer selection.
Great beer selections as well as meals. The grilled cheese with tomato soup is quite delicious.
Great place, friendly staff. I had the Black n Bleu steak salad ... perfect for lunch
Where else can you go?  Sigh.
Great place
Upscale bar. But not to upscale.
Very rude waiters and the least bit helpful, food was okay.
Burgers were good. Close proximity to the capitol buildings. Quickly got in our group of 10 during lunch hour.
Its ok but the congressmen that visit make me want to vomit out a bald eagle onto their plates and ask them why they are stupid
Absolutely amazing food and service. They also have reasonably priced drinks.

Did a decent job of handling the huge crowds from the women's March on Washington. I have no idea how they operate normally. I was a bit surprised, they stopped taking food orders since they were so overwhelmed.
Very happening location, especially with the weekday lunch crowd.  Buffalo chicken sandwich is amazing
Great food and atmosphere

Great food, service, and atmosphere. Our waiter was wonderful and we got our food quickly. There mac and cheese is great and my mother loved her burger. Nice place to grab a quick but delisous lunch. Definatly recomend.
Food is always good. Awesome apple cobbler!

Better food at chain restaurant. .....took 30 mins for a drink when the place was NOT even half full, food had no flavor and the EXTREEEEEEEEEEEEMELY slow server could not get our order or bill correct.  The only good I would say about this place is that you could use the restroom without eating there......aint nobody gonna stop you cause they are arguing with a patron about the extra stuff on the bill.  I vote that they close and reopen under new management and hire servers that are not sloths and speak so you can hear or understand them.
Food was delicious. Service was pretty awful. But the food made up for it. Prices were very reasonable for the DC area.
The food was good.
Great place. Here you can find Senators and House Representatives meeting with their constituents.
The Burger on a Stick is scary amazing!
Cool place good food
Good food with nice outdoor seating in a central location.
Ok
Good beer list, fun atmosphere.
Great spot for a beer. Lots of politics from the Hill.
A friendly atmosphere with very kind bar tenders. It maybe serve as a great chill place if you just spent long hours in the library of congress to walk down the street to.
The Arugula and Strawberry salads are delicious!! And Tender Chicken  as well

Can't rate the food because both times we attempted to go there, they told us they were closed.  Either the website has the wrong hours or the staff is shutting down several hours too early.  Disappointing.
The food is alright as far as bar food goes. The tap selection was decent and they had purple haze on draft which was a nice surprise. Every now and then I need a fix of my old local beer.
Great eatery, friendly staff
Good.
Loved this place! Food was great and it was walking distance to the Capitol. One of the better places we have bend to eat in D.C.
It's loud, and the unique shake choices don't always taste as good as they sound.
I really liked the atmosphere and the service was great! Slight changes to the food (a little more attention), would give this place the 5th star it's looking for. The beer was great though!!

After a great day at the Cherry Blossom Festval, we walked to Bullfeathers for dinner. Our server, Cami, made us feel welcome with a couple of Amber drafts. We had the calamari with a great dipping sauce. The portion was huge as well as delicious. We had buffalo wings as well which were crispy and nicely spiced. We enjoyed the food and certainly appreciated being so well taken care of by Cami!
Met up with some friends and sat out front on the patio. Such a great spot being so close to the Capitol, their food was also pretty good.
Nice environment, decent food, friendly staff
Good service,  just beat the rush.  Food was good,  decent sized lunch portions.  Little expensive but it's dc.
I was s bartender during REAGAN/BUSH.fun times!

Often packed, average food. The price is slightly higher than what you should pay for this quality of food, but you're not really overpaying. Service is fine. Eat here today and try to tell me in a month what you ordered.
Get the "The Teddy" and the buffalo eggplant chips and have a great time. That is all.

I have been going back to this place for years, every time I come to the DC area.  My wife loves it, took my brother there and he loves it.  He now takes people there when he stays in DC.  Nice location to the National Mall/Capitol too. The burgers are awesome and the beer is cold.  My favorite DC place to eat.
Tourist Trap
Burgers were good but the service wasn't fabulous.

Bullfeathers is a traditional after work place for many government employees and I have come here a few times. The service seems to be either very good or terrible. The food can be good but prices are on the high side. I cringe when I have to pay more than $10 for a burger.
One of my favorite spots for almost 30 years. D.C. Saloons of this caliber are fading due inflated leases. Somehow,  Bullfeathers marches on... Bully!

Delicious food! ! Got a turkey club.  Ingredients seemed to be really fresh. Husband got a burger sandwich. Meat was really good. Food was juicy and delicious! Worth the cost. Portions are quit large, could share one sandwich with two people.  Place was clean and staff really nice.  Would definitely come back!
Best cuban sandwich! Freshly baked bread and tasty condiments! Bravo!!!

Went there for lunch. The very nice waiter recommended the daily special, a New York strip steak sandwich, which I ordered. The sandwich smelled incredibly spoiled and I had to send it back. Ruined my appetite completely.  They have a very impressive milkshake menu, including classics such as bacon pancake flavour or captain crunch. I chickened out with a caramel, which was ok, except for the ending which most of all resembled butter.  I won't be coming back.

The service wasn't the greatest but it was pretty good. But the burgers are amazing and the restaurant has a nice atmosphere. The corn bread served before your meal is some of the best I've ever had and being from the south it's tough to find good corn bread in a  restaurant.

The service was fantastic, we had spent all day wandering through the museums with 3 kids ages from teenager down to 6 years old.  Our server made every one comfortable.  The food was unbelievably excellent, I had the Big Stick Burger, that we found out after being served had been just added to the menu and I was the first to order, I highly recommend this burger to all Burger enthusiasts, the place is small but very clean and comfortable.  When we go back to DC we will be visiting Bullyfeathers again.........

We ate lunch here and the place was packed. And I know why. The burgers were awesome. Very thick and juicy. The girl that waited on us was just ok. We wanted to order another round of drinks but she was too busy running around behind the bar. When she finally showed up we just got our check and left. But worth the stop I'm sure they have better wait staff. Would go back for the food.

I dined there with a few friends of mine in June 2012.  It's near a Capital South DC metro station, making it easy to walk to.  We took advantage of the nice weather and dined outside.  I enjoyed the steak,  and the strawberry shortcake was delicious.  For the record, the food was 2.5/3.  The waiter service was polite and engaging.    Our meals matched our orders, and our table well attended by the waiter.  I would recommend this restaurant, and plan on returning.
Great burgers and chicken sandwiches. Decent selection of beers.
